<font color="#FF0000">COMMENTS FOR DOC SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug  7  1:02:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc Spatz,<br><br>
Interesting.<br><br>
I think Richard can speak for himself, can't he? Have you become his self appointed ersatz mouthpiece? He should be able to respond to Ed and to my post as well, all by himself, or have you relegated him to the status of a wheezy wind up Victrola and a stack of un-intelligible Caruso records so we can do nothing but listen to you?<br><br>
You seem to have used the protective &quot;how dare you&quot; gambit for Ricahrd as an excuse to justify and continue your comments to Ed. Your comments, however say nothing, and do not dignify your position in any way.<br><br>
Just as a matter of historical reminder, I see it was you who started this fight by picking at the poetry/literary contributions to this site a while back in a way that was  undignified, uncalled for, and demonstrated an enormous talent for intolerance and bigotry, two unenviable qualities that have clearly manifest themselves here. <br><br>
Your attempts to use apology and a claim of satire are lame excuses to create an illusion that this behavior is intelligent. It isn't. Furthermore, prior comments concerning Native American contributions, campfires, and the like, only cement the blocks of the wall you have built around yourself. <br><br>
I suggest you look at your last comments to Ed as a mirror to yourself. That's the way I see it.<br><br>
Clearly Ed has a srongly held point of view on the Vietnam War, he obviously does not hold your views in high esteem, and he can take care of himself even in the best of exchanges. Good for him. He went through hell in 'Nam with the rest of us, and maybe a little more than most. For that accomplishment of survival alone he should be given a modicum of respect and understanding, for, after all, weren't you against the War in which he, and many of the rest of us found ourselves stuck through no fault of our own? I would think that you would be empathetic to the War's victims. Instead I see pure narcissistic rage. I recall you telling me once &quot;...admit it, you suck...&quot;. It seems we are full circle, and, I for one, grow weary of your strategy. Actually, bored is more like it. Really repetitious. <br><br>
A close personal friend e-mailed to me comments. He is an avid reader, and follower of this site, and a fellow 'Nam Vet, a spook 'Nam Vet at that. He never posts. In a completely unsolicited manner, he said:<br><br>
&quot;I visited the thread.  Doc is active as is Mustang two four and Edward. Doc's mouth so elevates my rage that I can barely restrain verbally dismantling the asshole.  If there was ever an unredeamable traitorous sack of shit, I have found it.  I promised a long time ago I would watch<br>
because I suffer alone.  I am not sure I can restrain myself.  He tests even my patience.<br><br>
Sorry friend, but this guy deserves no mercy.  In the biblical sense<br>
&quot;If thine eye offends thee, pluck it out&quot;<br><br>
Peace&quot; <br><br>
It seems that you have finally pissed off even the spooks. Don't worry if you do not understand the meaning of spook in this context. No one would tell you, anyway. <br><br>
So, Doc, we don't seem to be farther along in really understanding things than those who were afraid of the monsters at the edge of the flat world a ling time ago. Just think, who would have thought that a war fought 30 years ago still lives and spawns, again and again.<br><br>
I hate reincarnation, don't you?<br><br>
See you around.<br><br>
   <br><br>

